A machinist creates a milling template that is composed of two shapes, as shown.

\begin{itemize}
\item A rectangle with a length of $13$ centimeters and a height of $4$ centimeters.
\item A square with side length $5$ centimeters.
\end{itemize}

Find the total area, in centimeters, of the template.

\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw (0,0) rectangle (3.25,1);
\draw (2,1) rectangle (3.25,2.25);
\node at (3.5,0.5) {4 cm};
\node at (1.625,-0.3) {13 cm};
\node at (2.625,2.5) {5 cm};
\end{tikzpicture}

\begin{enumerate}
\item[a.] $22$ square centimeters
\item[b.] $25$ square centimeters
\item[c.] $77$ square centimeters
\item[d.] $260$ square centimeters
\end{enumerate}
